name: chinook-salmon-evolutionarily-significant-units
notes: These data represent the final delineated population boundaries associated with salmonid Evolutionarily Significant Units (ESU) for the four recovery domains in the Pacific Northwest. These boundaries were designated by federally-mandated Technical Recovery Teams (TRTs) each covering a recovery domain; Puget Sound, Willamette-Lower Columbia, Interior Columbia, and the Oregon/Northern California Coast.
